Anthony O’BOYLE, Libelant Appellant, v. Steam Tug SENATOR RICE, Her Engines, etc.; Cornell Steamboat Company, Claimant Appellee. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. November 1, 1926.) No. 40. Horace L. Cheyney and Macklin, Brown & Van Wyck, all of New York City, for appellant. Robert S. Erskine, Henry P. Elliott, and Kirlin, Woolsey, Campbell, Hiekox & Keating, all of New York City, for appellee. ,

Before HOUGH, MANTON, and MACK, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree (15 F.[2d] 882) affirmed, with costs.
